obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9624)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and Commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9624&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Judges (Inquiry) Act, 1968.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st January, 1969, vide notification No. G.S.R. 35, dated the 1st January, 1969, see Gazette of India, 1969, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9625)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9625&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(b) "Committee" means a Committee constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Judge" means a Judge of the Supreme Court or of a High Court and includes the Chief`
  line `Justice of India and the Chief Justice of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Speaker" means the Speaker of the House of the People.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9626)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Investigation into misbehaviour or incapacity of Judge by Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9626&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If notice is`
  line `given of a motion for presenting an address to the President praying for the removal of a`
  line `Judge signed,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a notice given in the House of the People, by not less than one hundred`
  line `members of that House;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a notice given in the Council of States, by not less than fifty members of`
  line `that Council;`
  line
  line `then, the Speaker or, as the case may be, the Chairman may, after consulting such persons, if any, as`
  line `he thinks fit and after considering such materials, if any, as may be available to him, either admit the`
  line `motion or refuse to admit the same.`
  line
  line `(2) If the motion referred to in sub-section (1) is admitted, the Speaker or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Chairman shall keep the motion pending and constitute, as soon as may be, for the purpose of making`
  line `an investigation into the grounds on which the removal of a Judge is prayed for, a Committee`
  line `consisting of three members of whom--`
  line
  line `(a) one shall be chosen from among the Chief Justice and other Judges of the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(b) one shall be chosen from among the Chief Justices of the High Courts, and`
  line
  line `(c) one shall be a person who is, in the opinion of, the Speaker or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Chairman, a distinguished jurist:`
  line
  line `Provided that where notices of a motion referred to in sub-section (1) are given on the same day in`
  line `both Houses of Parliament, no Committee shall be constituted unless the motion has been admitted in`
  line `both Houses and where such motion has been admitted in both Houses, the Committee shall be`
  line `constituted jointly by the Speaker and the Chairman:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where notices of a motion as aforesaid are given in the Houses of Parliament`
  line `on different dates, the notice which is given later shall stand rejected.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall frame definite charges against the Judge on the basis of which the`
  line `investigation is proposed to be held.`
  line
  line `(4) Such charges together with a statement of the grounds on which each such charge is based`
  line `shall be communicated to the Judge and he shall be given a reasonable opportunity of presenting a`
  line `written statement of defence within such time as may be specified in this behalf by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) Where it is alleged that the Judge is unable to discharge the duties of his office efficiently due`
  line `to any physical or mental incapacity and the allegation is denied, the Committee may arrange for the`
  line `medical examination of the Judge by such Medical Board as may be appointed for the purpose by the`
  line `Speaker or, as the case may be, the Chairman or, where the Committee is constituted jointly by the`
  line `Speaker and the Chairman, by both of them, for the purpose and the Judge shall submit himself to`
  line `such medical examination within the time specified in this behalf by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) The Medical Board shall undertake such medical examination of the Judge as may be`
  line `considered necessary and submit a report to the Committee stating therein whether the incapacity is`
  line `such as to render the Judge unfit to continue in office.`
  line
  line `(7) If the Judge refuses to undergo medical examination considered necessary by the Medical`
  line `Board, the Board shall submit a report to the Committee stating therein the examination which the`
  line `Judge has refused to undergo, and the Committee may, on receipt of such report, presume that the`
  line `Judge suffers from such physical or mental incapacity as is alleged in the motion referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(8) The Committee may, after considering the written statement of the Judge and the medical`
  line `report, if any, amend the charges framed under sub-section (3) and in such a case, the Judge shall be`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of presenting a fresh written statement of defence.`
  line
  line `(9) The Central Government may, if required by the Speaker or the Chairman, or both, as the case`
  line `may be, appoint an advocate to conduct the case against the Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9627)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Report of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9627&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the`
  line `Committee shall have power to regulate its own procedure in making the investigation and shall give`
  line `a reasonable opportunity to the Judge of cross-examining witnesses, adducing evidence and of being`
  line `heard in his defence.`
  line
  line `(2) At the conclusion of the investigation, the Committee shall submit its report to the Speaker or,`
  line `as the case may be, to the Chairman, or where the Committee has been constituted jointly by the`
  line `Speaker and the Chairman, to both of them, stating therein its findings on each of the charges`
  line `separately with such observations on the whole case as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Speaker or the Chairman or, where the Committee has been constituted jointly by the`
  line `Speaker and the Chairman, both of them, shall cause the report submitted under sub-section (2) to be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be, respectively before the House of the People and the Council of States.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9628)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9628&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of making any investigation under this Act the`
  line `Committee shall have the powers of a civil court, while trying a suit, under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on oath;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9629)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Consideration of report and procedure for presentation of an address for removal of Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9629&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the report of the Committee contains a finding that the Judge is not guilty of any misbehaviour or does not suffer from any incapacity, then no further steps shall be taken in either`
  line `House of Parliament in relation to the report and the motion pending in the House or the Houses of`
  line `Parliament shall not be proceeded with.`
  line
  line `(2) If the report of the Committee contains a finding that the Judge is guilty of any misbehaviour`
  line `or suffers from any incapacity, then, the motion referred to in sub-section (1) of section 3 shall,`
  line `together with the report of the Committee, be taken up for consideration by the House or the Houses`
  line `of Parliament in which it is pending.`
  line
  line `(3) If the motion is adopted by each House of Parliament in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `clause (4) of article 124 or, as the case may be, in accordance with that clause read with article 218 of`
  line `the Constitution, then, the misbehaviour or incapacity of the Judge shall be deemed to have been`
  line `proved and an address praying for the removal of the Judge shall be presented in the prescribed`
  line `manner to the President by each House of Parliament in the same session in which the motion has`
  line `been adopted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9630)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594&sectionId=9630&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00008_196851_1517807319594
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Joint Committee of both Houses of`
  line `Parliament in accordance with the provisions hereinafter contained for the purpose of making rules to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Joint Committee shall consist of fifteen members of whom ten shall be nominated by the`
  line `Speaker and five shall be nominated by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(3) The Joint Committee shall elect its own Chairman and shall have power to regulate its`
  line `own procedure.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Joint Committee`
  line `may make rules to provide for the following among other matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of transmission of a motion adopted in one House to the other House of`
  line Parliament;
  line
  line `(b) the manner of presentation of an address to the President for the removal of a Judge;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and other allowances payable to the members of the Committee and the`
  line `witnesses who may be required to attend such Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) the facilities which may be accorded to the Judge for defending himself;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be, or may be, provided for by rules or in respect of which`
  line `provision is, in the opinion of the Joint Committee, necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) Any rules made under this section shall not take effect until they are approved and confirmed`
  line `both by the Speaker and the Chairman and are published in the Official Gazette, and such publication`
  line `of the rules shall be conclusive proof that they have been duly made.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
